    <briefdescription>
<para>HMAC-SHA256 — keyed-hash message authentication code. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Built on top of syn_sha256. Provides the same streaming pattern: init (with key) → update → final</para>
<para>The context wraps two SHA-256 contexts (~224 bytes caller-owned). No heap, no external dependencies.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Usage</title><para><programlisting><codeline><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>One-shot:</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">uint8_t<sp/>mac[32];</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__hmac_8h_1a8756a6bdfa948349ef3aff050ce40ca3" kindref="member">syn_hmac_sha256</ref>(key,<sp/>key_len,<sp/>message,<sp/>msg_len,<sp/>mac);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>Streaming:</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="structSYN__HMAC__SHA256" kindref="compound">SYN_HMAC_SHA256</ref><sp/>ctx;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__hmac_8h_1a6067f8ebcdec74b2b877caad3380df56" kindref="member">syn_hmac_sha256_init</ref>(&amp;ctx,<sp/>key,<sp/>key_len);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__hmac_8h_1a9071c35fe8ffef2e89762b2090594255" kindref="member">syn_hmac_sha256_update</ref>(&amp;ctx,<sp/>chunk1,<sp/>len1);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__hmac_8h_1a9071c35fe8ffef2e89762b2090594255" kindref="member">syn_hmac_sha256_update</ref>(&amp;ctx,<sp/>chunk2,<sp/>len2);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="syn__hmac_8h_1a79f9790e1355ed0efeaf1ca745729d6e" kindref="member">syn_hmac_sha256_final</ref>(&amp;ctx,<sp/>mac);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting> </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
